I. Prerequisites
----------------

The following Perl modules are required:

  LWP::UserAgent
  HTTP::Request::Common
  URI::Escape
  Term::ReadKey        (optional — enables hidden org-key entry in interactive mode)

Install via your system package manager:

  apt install libwww-perl libterm-readkey-perl   # Debian / Ubuntu

Or via CPAN:

  cpan LWP::UserAgent HTTP::Request::Common URI::Escape Term::ReadKey

If modules are installed to a non-standard path (e.g. via cpanm to ~/perl5),
add the library path with -I:

  perl -I~/perl5/lib/perl5 cdse_client.pl [OPTIONS] COMMAND [ARGS...]

The automated test suite sets this automatically.


II. Credentials
---------------

Source the env.sh file in the parent directory to export credentials for
the included development installation:

  source ../env.sh

This exports:

  CDSE_SERVER   = https://localhost:8443
  CDSE_USER_ID  = EngineAdmin
  CDSE_ORG_ID   = EngineOrg
  CDSE_ORG_KEY  = 187465950C5F9018D04F91E976CAC1D7FA19CBA5FE26D94038630B18BCBAAAB6
  CDSE_STORAGE  = EngineStorage

All examples below assume these variables are exported.  The equivalent
flags are shown in Section IV for reference.

Never pass the org key on the command line in production — it appears in
shell history and process listings.  Prefer the CDSE_ORG_KEY environment
variable or interactive mode.


III. Quick start
----------------

  # Source the development credentials
  source ../env.sh

  # Verify the engine is reachable
  perl cdse_client.pl --insecure info

  # Store a file as an encrypted secret
  echo "top secret payload" > /tmp/payload.txt
  perl cdse_client.pl --insecure store-secret demo-secret /tmp/payload.txt

  # Retrieve it to stdout
  perl cdse_client.pl --insecure get-secret demo-secret

  # Clean up
  perl cdse_client.pl --insecure delete-secret demo-secret

For HTTP (BYPASSTLSAUTHINHTTP build) replace --insecure with
--server http://localhost:8080.


IV. Command reference
---------------------

Usage:
  perl cdse_client.pl [OPTIONS] COMMAND [ARGS...]

Options:

  --server HOST          CaumeDSE server URL or host:port.
                         Default: $CDSE_SERVER or localhost:8443.
                         If no scheme is given, https:// is prepended.
  --userId USER_ID       userId credential.  Default: $CDSE_USER_ID.
  --orgId ORG_ID         orgId credential.   Default: $CDSE_ORG_ID.
  --orgKey ORG_KEY       orgKey (encryption key).  Default: $CDSE_ORG_KEY.
                         Prefer the environment variable or interactive mode.
  --storage STORAGE      Storage bucket name.  Default: $CDSE_STORAGE or
                         EngineStorage.
  --ca-cert FILE         Path to a PEM CA certificate for TLS verification.
                         Example: --ca-cert /opt/cdse/ca.pem
  --insecure             Disable TLS certificate verification.
                         Development/local testing only.
  --interactive / -i     Enter interactive REPL mode after credential setup.

Commands:

  info
      Show userId, orgId, role, and storage information for the
      authenticated user.

  list-secrets
      List the names of all encrypted raw-file secrets in the storage,
      as CSV output.

  store-secret NAME FILE [INFO]
      Upload FILE and store it as an AES-256-GCM encrypted secret named NAME.
      INFO is optional free-text metadata attached to the document.

  get-secret NAME [OUTFILE]
      Retrieve and decrypt the secret named NAME.  If OUTFILE is given, the
      binary content is written there; otherwise it is printed to stdout.

  delete-secret NAME
      Permanently delete the secret named NAME.

  db-list
      List the names of all encrypted CSV database documents, as CSV.

  db-create NAME col1,col2,...
      Create a new encrypted CSV database named NAME.  Columns are given as a
      comma-separated list with no spaces.

  db-insert NAME col=val ...
      Append one row to database NAME.  Each column value is a col=val pair.
      Columns not specified remain empty.

  db-query NAME [ROW]
      Print all rows of database NAME as CSV, or print only row ROW (1-based)
      if specified.

  db-update NAME ROW col=val ...
      Update one or more columns in row ROW of database NAME.

  db-delete-row NAME ROW
      Delete row ROW from database NAME.

  db-delete NAME
      Delete the entire CSV database document NAME.

  audit-log
      Retrieve and print the engine's transaction audit log as CSV.

  help
      Print the usage block from the top of cdse_client.pl.


V. Secrets — full walkthrough
------------------------------

Prepare a test secret file:

  echo "AES-256 master key material" > /tmp/master.key

Store the secret with optional metadata:

  perl cdse_client.pl --insecure \
      store-secret master-key /tmp/master.key "AES-256 key for prod DB"

Expected output:
  <html>...<b>200 OK - Document resource created...</b>...

List all stored secrets:

  perl cdse_client.pl --insecure list-secrets

Expected output (CSV with document metadata):
  documentId,...
  master-key,...

Retrieve the secret to a file:

  perl cdse_client.pl --insecure \
      get-secret master-key /tmp/master-retrieved.key

Expected output:
  Secret saved to: /tmp/master-retrieved.key

Verify the round-trip:

  diff /tmp/master.key /tmp/master-retrieved.key

Retrieve to stdout:

  perl cdse_client.pl --insecure get-secret master-key

Expected output:
  AES-256 master key material

Delete the secret:

  perl cdse_client.pl --insecure delete-secret master-key

Expected output:
  <html>...<b>200 OK - Document resource deleted...</b>...


VI. Encrypted CSV database — full walkthrough
----------------------------------------------

Create the database:

  perl cdse_client.pl --insecure db-create contacts id,name,email,phone

Insert rows:

  perl cdse_client.pl --insecure \
      db-insert contacts id=1 name=Alice email=alice@example.com phone=555-0100

  perl cdse_client.pl --insecure \
      db-insert contacts id=2 name=Bob email=bob@example.com phone=555-0200

  perl cdse_client.pl --insecure \
      db-insert contacts id=3 name=Carol email=carol@example.com phone=555-0300

Query all rows:

  perl cdse_client.pl --insecure db-query contacts

Expected output (CSV):
  id,name,email,phone
  1,Alice,alice@example.com,555-0100
  2,Bob,bob@example.com,555-0200
  3,Carol,carol@example.com,555-0300

Query a specific row (1-based index):

  perl cdse_client.pl --insecure db-query contacts 2

Expected output:
  id,name,email,phone
  2,Bob,bob@example.com,555-0200

Update row 1:

  perl cdse_client.pl --insecure \
      db-update contacts 1 email=alice@newdomain.com phone=555-9999

Verify the update:

  perl cdse_client.pl --insecure db-query contacts 1

Expected output:
  id,name,email,phone
  1,Alice,alice@newdomain.com,555-9999

Delete row 3:

  perl cdse_client.pl --insecure db-delete-row contacts 3

Delete the entire database:

  perl cdse_client.pl --insecure db-delete contacts

Confirm removal:

  perl cdse_client.pl --insecure db-list


VII. Interactive mode
---------------------

Start interactive mode.  Credentials not supplied as flags are prompted;
the org key is hidden if Term::ReadKey is available:

  perl cdse_client.pl --insecure --interactive

Or supply some credentials as flags:

  perl cdse_client.pl --insecure -i \
      --server https://localhost:8443 \
      --userId EngineAdmin --orgId EngineOrg

When prompted, leave a field blank to keep its current value (from env
variables or flags).

At the cdse> prompt, type commands without credentials:

  cdse> info
  cdse> store-secret mykey /tmp/key.bin "optional description"
  cdse> list-secrets
  cdse> get-secret mykey /tmp/out.bin
  cdse> delete-secret mykey
  cdse> db-create vault id,secret,label
  cdse> db-insert vault id=1 secret=abc123 label=dev
  cdse> db-query vault
  cdse> db-update vault 1 label=production
  cdse> db-delete-row vault 1
  cdse> db-delete vault
  cdse> audit-log
  cdse> help
  cdse> quit

Press Ctrl-D or type quit/exit to leave the session.


VIII. Environment variable reference
--------------------------------------

  CDSE_SERVER    Base URL or host:port of the CDSE instance.
                 Default: localhost:8443
                 Example: https://myserver:8443
                          http://localhost:8080  (BYPASSTLSAUTHINHTTP build)

  CDSE_USER_ID   userId credential.
                 Example: EngineAdmin

  CDSE_ORG_ID    orgId credential.
                 Example: EngineOrg

  CDSE_ORG_KEY   Organisation encryption key.  No default — must be set.
                 Example: 187465950C5F9018D04F91E976CAC1D7FA19CBA5FE26D94038630B18BCBAAAB6
                 (development installation key; see ../env.sh)

  CDSE_STORAGE   Storage bucket name.
                 Default: EngineStorage

Command-line flags override environment variables.


IX. TLS options
---------------

Verify the server using the included development CA certificate:

  perl cdse_client.pl --ca-cert /opt/cdse/ca.pem info

Disable verification (development only):

  perl cdse_client.pl --insecure info

Use HTTP (BYPASSTLSAUTHINHTTP build, no TLS):

  perl cdse_client.pl --server http://localhost:8080 info

Never use --insecure or the HTTP port in production.


X. Exit codes
-------------

  0   Success.
  1   Missing credential, unknown command, or API error.
